My sweet girl❤️ I had to say goodbye to my best friend of 14 years last night. We don’t deserve the unconditional love our doggies give us. I’ll miss you so much Jessie girl you brought me so many amazing memories, comforted me while I cried, got me through middle school, saved me in high school, and waved me off to college. go kiss your dogs right now and squeeze em tight. I’ll love you forever Jessie girl ❤️

Today the world lost a beautiful person and I’d like to share him with you guys. He kept the whole family laughing always. He loved telling his same stories over and over but we listened every time! He loved his pajama pants and he loved the bruins even more. I can only imagine the big hug nana pat gave you this morning in heaven pa. Times like this really put into perspective how important the people we love are, how important family is. Make sure to hug everyone you love and make sure you tell them you love them. Life is precious ❤️

2023 what a fucking year!!!! This year was as challenging as it was rewarding. Crushed two tours with my best friend, created and hosted my own reality show, watched pirate water take off, got lost at sea, met the loml, got Boston my built in best friend, got to bring my family along to experience a little bit of my job, traveled across the world a few times, stayed level headed while the whole internet tore me apart, and sososo much more but most importantly enjoyed every single moment even the lows. I’m so beyond blessed and grateful to live this life and I cannot wait to see what 2024 brings. I love you guys and thanks for being along for the journey always🥹
